Class Employee

java.lang.Object
cyprusDryCleanEntities.Employee
public class Employee extends Object
Employee Class represents an employee with personal details. This class is used to store and retrieve employee information.
Version:
23.0
Author:
Ferhat Kasim Koc

    • Employee

      public Employee(int employeeId, String name, String surname)
      This constructor is initializing an employee with basic personal information. No need to provide Birth Date or Starting Date
      Parameters:
      employeeId - the unique identifier for the employee
      name - the first name of the employee
      surname - the last name of the employee

    • Employee

      public Employee(int employeeId, String name, String surname, Date dateOfBirth, Date startDate)
      This constructor is used to initialize an employee with all fields.
      Parameters:
      employeeId - the unique identifier for the employee
      name - the first name of the employee
      surname - the last name of the employee
      dateOfBirth - the Birth Date of the employee
      startDate - the date the employee started work
